were blocks of buildings let out in chambers and flats. In these the great bulk of the population of Rome was housed.

CHAPTER XLVI.

1. Hoc] This seems to refer to the plans of Macro with regard to Caius Caesar as well as to the immediately preceding sentence. All was known to the emperor, both these plans and

the young man's character.

2. Nepotes] The son of Drusus (his name was Tiberius,) the emperor’s own grandson, and Gaius, the son of Germanicus.
